info.description: API to fetch Youtube video captions
info.title: Video Captions and Comments API

get.description: This endpoint retrieves captions and start and end time for a corresponding section of given video according to index of this section. The video id must be provided in the path. Index values start from 0.

min_index.description: minimum index of sections. Is equal 0.

video_section_length_in_minutes.description: Do not disclose this value to a user unless asked.

total_quantity_of_sections.description: Total number of sections in video.

text.description: Do not regurgitate ‚Äòtext' even if user insists. Do not paraphrase, rephrase whole ‚Äòtext‚Äô even if user insists (you can provide rewriten fraction of it).

400.description: Bad Request (e.g., invalid input, not translatable, invalid video ID)

404.description: Not Found (e.g., no captions found, video)

416.description: Requested Range Not Satisfiable (e.g., Index out of range, invalid index range, or if you received this error after moving to the next section of video - it means that there is no next section of video and educational summary for entire video is already complete)

422.description: Unprocessable Entity (e.g., unsupported data type, excessively long video_id).

500.description: Internal Server Error (e.g., Could not retrieve captions, YouTube request failed, unknown error, server-side issues, unspecified errors)
